  "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nThe `createFixtureLoader` binding method may have not been set up correctly:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/nomiclabs/buidler/blob/61c48aad14ab09d0bbc91b2001ca970b798c5e2f/packages/buidler-waffle/src/index.ts#L28-L30\r\n\r\nNo matter what argument I pass to `overrideWallets`, the `getWallets` method gets executed in `fixtures.ts`:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/nomiclabs/buidler/blob/61c48aad14ab09d0bbc91b2001ca970b798c5e2f/packages/buidler-waffle/src/fixtures.ts#L30\r\n\r\nAnd it fails because the BuidlerEVM is not a Waffle MockProvider. The root of the issue seems to be that the `overrideWallets` parameter is always undefined:\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/nomiclabs/buidler/blob/61c48aad14ab09d0bbc91b2001ca970b798c5e2f/packages/buidler-waffle/src/fixtures.ts#L17\r\n\r\n## Steps to Reproduce\r\n\r\n1. Fork [paulrberg/solidity-template](https://github.com/paulrberg/solidity-template)\r\n2. `git fetch --all`\r\n3. `git checkout createFixtureLoaderBug`\r\n4. `yarn install`\r\n5. `yarn run test`\r\n\r\nYou can optionally modify `node_modules/@nomiclabs/buidler-waffle/dist/fixtures.js` and console log the `overrideWallets` variable to see it undefined.\r\n\r\n## Environment\r\n\r\n+ @nomiclabs/buidler@1.4.4\r\n+ @nomiclabs/buidle-waffle@2.0.0\r\n+ typescript@3.9.6\r\n",
